OL,6,FThe Department for Levelling Up,
OL,7,FHousing and Communities (DLUHC) begins
OL,8,Fmonitoring Warrington Borough Council
OL,9,Fas it has "high levels of indebtedness
OL,10,Frelative to their revenue budgets,
OL,11,Freserves or Council Tax base".
OL,13,FThe DLUHC commissions the Chartered
OL,14,FInstitute of Public Finance and
OL,15,FAccountancy (CIPFA) to undertake a
OL,16,Fdetailed review of Warrington's
OL,17,Fcapital finances.
OL,19,FThe report is published, but it is not
OL,20,Fmade public for another 10 months, in
OL,21,FMay 2024.
